Here's a simple HTML web app that simulates the game where you have to bring Minran her red bag, with a 30% chance of choosing the correct one. The code includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for functionality.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Minran's Red Bag Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 50px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #28a745;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #218838;
        }
        .result {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Bring Minran Her Red Bag!</h1>
    <p>There is a 30% chance that the red bag you choose is the right one.</p>
    <button id="chooseBagButton">Choose a Red Bag</button>
    <div class="result" id="result"></div>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('chooseBagButton').addEventListener('click', function() {
            // Generate a random number between 0 and 1
            const chance = Math.random();
            const resultDiv = document.getElementById('result');

            // Check if the random number is less than 0.3 (30% chance)
            if (chance < 0.3) {
                resultDiv.textContent = "Congratulations! You brought the right red bag to Minran!";
                resultDiv.style.color = "green";
            } else {
                resultDiv.textContent = "Oops! That's not the right red bag. Try again!";
                resultDiv.style.color = "red";
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Paste it into a text editor and save it with a `.html` extension (e.g., `minran_red_bag_game.html`).
3. Open the saved file in a web browser to play the game. Click the button to see if you chose the correct red bag!
